It is actually a forever/infinite loop unless you break out of it with code like this:<p><pre><code>    var i = 0;
    for (;;) {
      log(i);
      i++;
      if (i > 10) {
        break;
      }
    };

</code></pre>
In a way is recursion, it is equivalent to this:<p><pre><code>    var i = 0;
    (function () {
       log(i);
       i++;
       if (i > 10) {
         return;
       }
      arguments.callee();
    })();</code></pre>
